<TEXT>
apparent hired assassins killed another 
seven policemen wednesday in colombia and a judge handling drug 
trafficking cases was shot to death authorities said 
three of the policemen were shot to death on the streets of the 
northwestern city of medellin headquarters of the worlds largest 
cocaine gang a spokesman with the police department said in a 
telephone interview 
the medellin cartel has unleashed a bloodbath against colombian 
policemen especially in that city the three deaths wednesday in 
medellin brought to 132 the number of policemen killed in that city 
in 1990 
the cartel has said it will pay about 4300 to gunmen for each 
policeman killed in colombia drug traffickers and government 
security forces have been locked in a deadly war since last 
augusts slaying of a presidential candidate who advocated 
extradition of drug suspects to the united states 
the police in medellin meanwhile deactivated a car bomb 
wednesday carrying 1000 pounds of dynamite the police spokesman 
said 
the dynamite was in a taxi and was armed with a fuse and 
detonators the policeman said the taxi was in a parking lot only 
about a halfblock from the city governments administrative office 
building 
it was the second car bomb deactivated in medellin in a week 
in the last 10 months the traffickers have responded with 283 
terrorist acts including one on a domestic airliner that have 
killed 274 people 
