queen elizabeth ii and her husband 
prince philip took a bus ride into icelands rugged interior to see 
the historic site of the worlds first parliament 
the drive on tuesday from reykjavik the capital to thingvellir 
where icelands legislature the althing was founded in 930 ad 
was the highlight of the threeday state visit which began monday 
the first by a british sovereign to iceland 
the royal couple took a lengthy walk down a rocky ravine to the 
lawspeakers rock where in ancient times an elected chieftain 
presided over the assembly 
the royal couple both passionately fond of horses also 
visited a stud farm that breeds the sturdy little horses of 
iceland which are known for their a gait that gives riders a 
comfortable seat 
