ceremonies tuesday he said welk symbolizes the talent of the 
descendants of germans who came to north dakota 100 years ago 
they are people who believe that artistic ability is at its 
best when it is for the common people the governor said 
welk knew early on he wanted to be a musician and not a farmer 
said rosemary schaefbauer president of welk heritage inc which 
is coordinating the restoration of the home where welk lived until 
he was 21 
he disliked milking the cows so he made it interesting by 
trying to do it in rhythm she said but the cows didnt like 
it they would kick over the milk pail or slap him with their 
tails 
young welk made a deal with his father lawrence would work on 
the farm until he was 21 if his father would buy him a 400 
accordion the deal complete he struck out on his own in 1924 
welk formed a band three years later and got his start in radio 
at wnax in yankton sd the band was known as the honolulu fruit 
gum orchestra and lawrence welk and his hotsy totsy boys and 
played at area ballrooms for several years in the late 1920s and 
early 1930s 
in the late 1930s the band traveled east to the william penn 
hotel in pittsburgh where champagne music was born welk 
played in the chicago area in the 1940s and became a national 
television star in the late 1950s 
his syndicated television show still in reruns is a favorite 
among north dakotans on saturday nights 
the bandleader now 87 and living in los angeles did not attend 
the groundbreaking but he sent a note of thanks 
little did i dream when i was growing up on the farm so many 
many years ago that someday it would be restored and people would 
come and marvel at how life was lived in the early 1920s welk 
wrote 
welks parents ludwig and christina arrived in north dakota in 
1893 
the welk farm in this town of 600 about 75 miles south of 
bismarck had been vacant since 1966 
the cost of the restoration project is estimated at 750000 
including 500000 for a trust to maintain the museum after it 
opens 
welk heritage inc has raised 150000 including 80000 from 
welks foundation in california it hopes to collect the rest from 
grants and donations 
