indicators in sedona ariz produced a consensus forecast of a 
weak 19 percent growth in the gross national product the 
nations total output of goods and services the gnp rose 3 percent 
last year and 44 percent in 1988 
but while consumers may be pulling back recent reports indicate 
that the manufacturing sector may have bottomed out bigticket 
durable goods orders for instance were up 39 percent in may 
while industrial production posted a 06 percent increase 
nevertheless the automobile and housing industries continue to 
be a drag on the economy leaving exports one of the few bright 
spots 
because of weak domestic demand the merrill lynch 
economists said exports are likely to be the main source of 
growth in the second quarter and for the rest of the year 
meanwhile the commerce department also said the index of 
leading economic indicators had slipped a revised 01 percent in 
april after a 10 percent gain in march but even though the index 
fell in april the revision was a slight improvement over the 02 
percent decline originally reported last month 
