with mexico 
american business would gain better access to a market of almost 
100 million mexicans mexico a strategically important neighbor of 
the united states would gain needed jobs and prosperity without a 
penny in additional aid from washington those are the principal 
benefits that could materialize from a proposed free trade pact 
between the united states and mexico 
in a recent meeting in washington president bush and carlos 
salinas de gortari president of mexico committed themselves in 
principle to easing barriers to the flow of capital goods and 
services between the two neighbors 
since jobs are being exported away why not steer them towards 
mexico where a significant percentage of the new wages would be 
spent on american goods and services and more prosperity in mexico 
might actually ease the already high levels of migration of mexican 
workers to the united states 
mr bush and mr salinas are realistic about the obstacles 
ahead but the idea is worth pursuing 
