<TEXT>
the making of a statement are the best indicators of reliability i 
doubt this is so in every instance and if it were true in a 
particular case that does not warrant ignoring other indicators of 
reliability such as corroborating evidence absent some other 
reason for excluding it 
in this case the younger daughters statements are corroborated 
by other evidence these facts coupled with the circumstances 
surrounding the making of the statements acknowledged by the court 
as suggesting that the statements are reliable give rise to a 
legitimate argument that admission of the statements did not 
violate the confrontation clause 
