soldiers convicted of harming civilians but this was the first 
known execution 
reporters who sought shelter in a shantytown near the barclay 
training center barracks heard numerous commands to ceasefire 
during the shooting but the commands were followed by bursts of 
gunfire from m16 rifles and screams from protesters and other 
civilians 
some witnesses speaking on condition of anonymity said they 
saw several demonstrators fall some apparently fell into open 
drains during a stampede to escape 
