after the incident including in the plush mamba point suburb where 
the us and other embassies are located 
a few hundred yards from the us embassy soldiers commandeered 
two cars and drive up and down the street leaning out of the 
windows and a sunroof firing occasional shots into the air 
thousands of people marched down monrovias main avenue on 
tuesday demanding does resignation but soldiers barred them from 
going near does palace 
tuesdays march headed by christian and moslem leaders was the 
first demonstration in monrovia calling for does resignation 
the president has refused rebel demands that he leave office 
immediately but he has agreed not to run for reelection next 
year the rebels led by former doe aide charles taylor accuse the 
