the bank from 1986 to 1988 
koskotas who was suspended as chairman oct 20 1988 fled his 
homeland as the scandal surrounding the greek socialist government 
heated up he was arrested nov 23 1988 at an airfield in bedford 
woodlocks ruling upheld a magistrates aug 24 1989 decision 
that koskotas could be extradited on felony charges but barred 
extradition on a misdemeanor travel documents charge 
