flying in the face of the scientific evidence all they are going 
to do is precipitate lawsuits 
at issue is the administrations plan announced tuesday to 
save the owl placed on the endangered species list last week with 
far milder reductions in the timber harvest than environmentalists 
had said were needed 
the administration says it can protect the shy twofoottall 
owl by reducing timber harvest levels from federal bureau of land 
management forests from 950 million board feet annually to 750 
million board feet 
the administrations plan announced by blm director cy jamison 
will cost an estimated 1000 jobs over two years compared with the 
governments prediction of an 8000job loss this decade under an 
earlier plan by forest service biologist jack ward thomas 
congressional and environmentalist critics of the plan charged 
the administration was ignoring evidence that current forest 
management practices are inadequate to reverse shrinkinghabitat 
and decliningpopulation trends jeopardizing the owls survival 
environmentalists say northwest timber harvests must be cut 
nearly in half to ensure that the owl will survive 
vento said he was also angry about agriculture secretary clayton 
