stephen solarz dny to provide 7 million in nonlethal aid to 
the coalition opposing cambodias vietnameseinstalled government 
that replaced language in the bill barring any aid to the 
resistance a prohibition supported by members who feared the 
dominance of the khmer rouge in the coalition 
the khmer rouge ruled cambodia in the 1970s and were responsible 
for the deaths of more than 1 million people in what have come to 
be known as the killing fields they are the strongest military 
faction in a coalition which also receives millions of dollars in 
covert us military aid 
