maintain at least the figment if not the reality of a third 
force in the country 
the bill is the principal vehicle for us military economic 
and development aid to friends and allies around the globe this 
years version begins what obey has called a planned 5year 
transition away from a past emphasis on military aid and toward 
economic support 
citing reduced eastwest tensions and an end to the cold war 
the house appropriations committee included new money for emerging 
democracies in eastern europe refugee and childrens programs and 
development in africa and latin america to pay for the increases 
the panel cut nearly 400 million from president bushs military 
aid request 
