the legislature gave final approval 
wednesday night to the strictest state abortion bill in the nation 
and passed it along to gov buddy roemer who has promised a veto 
the bill calls for prison terms of up to 10 years hard labor for 
doctors who perform abortions and offers no exceptions for women 
who wish to abort fetuses that are the product of rape or incest 
the bills sponsors hope to use it to challenge the us supreme 
courts 1973 roe vs wade decision legalizing abortion rights 
