<TEXT>
environmentalists charge that the bush 
administrations plans to balance the interests of northwest 
loggers against survival of the northern spotted owl are an assault 
on the endangered species act 
the administration tuesday announced preliminary plans for 
saving the owl by restricting logging the plan would cost 1000 
northwest logging jobs 
at the same time the administration asked for relaxation of the 
1973 endangered species act to let policymakers weigh the economic 
