<TEXT>
the christian shepherd of the east ecumenical 
patriarch dimitrios i next week begins a monthlong and 
unprecedented visit in the west with us church flocks 
a journey of love and unity he has called it 
its the first trip to this continent in history by a presiding 
spiritual leader of the 250 million eastern orthodox believers 
around the world about 7 million of them in the united states 
hes to take part in washington in a layclergy congress of the 
greek orthodox church led by archbishop iakovos meet with 
president bush and visit 10 other cities conferring with church 
leaders 
he seeks to further ecumenical rapprochement and to 
contribute to the cause of justice friendship and peace in the 
world iakovos said in an interview iakovos is deputy for the 
patriarch in the western hemisphere 
although eastern orthodoxy may seem unfamiliar to some 
westerners it wielded a powerful influence in the formative years 
of christianity and remains its principal flock in eastern europe 
it also has become a robust force in the americas and spurred 
by iakovos a vigorous participant in the ecumenical movement for 
christian unity has added a special dimension to it 
the ecumenical patriarch bishop of ancient constantinople now 
istanbul turkey holds a post in eastern orthodoxy somewhat 
similar to that of the pope the bishop of rome in roman 
catholicism 
however while the pope has direct juridical authority 
throughout that church the patriarch relies on intangible 
spiritual sway over mostly selfgoverning orthodox churches of 
various national origins 
he is considered primus inter pares first among equals of 
eastern orthodox patriarchs and bishops the 269th successor in an 
office traced back to the apostle andrew the papacy traces its 
orgins to the apostle peter 
eastern orthodox churches whether of greek russian bulgarian 
romanian or other cultural backgrounds have similar liturgies and 
hold the same doctrines based on undivided christianitys first 
seven ecumenical councils 
a central affirmation of faith is the nicene creed of 381 ad 
also commonly used in western churches of protestantism and roman 
catholicism 
despite basic unity however orthodoxy remains divided in this 
country into a dozen branches stemming from various national 
backgrounds yet all looking to dimitrios as preeminent spiritual 
guide 
metropolitan theodosius head of the russianderived orthodox 
church in america expressed hope the patriarchs visit will bring 
us orthodox groups into greater unity and harmony 
he personifies unity of all orthodox throughout the world 
theodosius said in a telephone interview we are hoping he will 
bring us closer to the full integration that we are looking for in 
our common efforts 
the millionmember oca is the second largest orthodox body in 
this country next to greek orthodoxy which numbers two million 
dimitrios a quiet unassuming man of 75 was born sept 8 
1914 in constantinople the new rome of the ancient byzantine 
empire which under turkish rule was renamed istanbul in 1930 
he served churches in greece turkey and iran and in 1972 was 
elected ecumenical patriarch succeeding athenagorus i an 
eloquent americanseasoned prelate 
the more reserved dimitrios initially stuck close to the 
patriarchate the sometimes harassed and restricted headquarters in 
heavily moslem turkey but lately has ventured among his flock 
around the world 
in 1987 he visited the soviet union conferring with prelates 
there including the late russian orthodox patriarch pimen 
succeeded in early june by patriarch alexi ii the visit was the 
first since 1589 
dimitrios also visited orthodox leaders in greece yugoslavia 
romania and poland and bulgaria and pope john paul ii at the 
vatican the world council of churches in geneva and archbishop of 
canterbury robert runcie in london 
until the mid20th century eastern orthodoxy had been isolated 
from western christianity for more than nine centuries since a 1054 
split between orthodoxy and roman catholicism 
at that time constantinoples patriarch and romes pope 
excommunicated each other 
but that prolonged rigid eastwest rift was healed when the 
late patriarch athenagorus and pope paul vi met and embraced in 
jerusalem in 1964 afterward the mutual excommunications were 
lifted 
eastern orthodoxy earlier in 1961 had joined the world council 
of churches previously made up mostly of western protestant 
denominations 
dimitrios whose office retains administrative ties with some 
orthodox bodies such as the large greek orthodox church of the 
americas has no such formal oversight of indepedent or 
autocephalous branches 
but he plans meetings with their leaders including those of the 
second largest us orthodox body the oca whose roots go back to 
the late 1700s in alaska before russia sold alaska to the united 
states in 1867 
most us orthodox churches arose through immigration of the 
late 19th and 20th centuries 
arriving in washington july 2 dimitrios spends 10 days there 
before visits in new york city hempstead n y allentown and 
johnstown pa san francisco chicago buffalo and niagara falls 
ny and boston 
