there was a time when the atlanta zoo was 
regarded as a kind of animal concentration camp a place where one 
keeper ate rabbits from the petting zoo and where other beasts 
lived and died unnaturally 
but that was before zoo director terry maple came along with his 
imagination and enthusiasm and organizational skills six years 
later and halfway through a 50 million renovation the atlanta zoo 
