<TEXT>
with cold wars thawing everywhere even 
americas two longfeuding teacher unions are talking peace 
the rival american federation of teachers and national education 
association lately have been aiming not at each other but at the 
bush administration and the nations governors for failing to 
advance muchheralded national education goals announced in 
february 
whats so frustrating said nea president keith geiger is 
that over the last six months weve heard how we have to allocate 
50 billion to bail out savings and loans but i find it 
interesting that nobody said we have to allocate another 74 
billion so we could fully fund head start i thought the education 
crisis was every bit as deep as the savings and loan crisis 
obviously it wasnt 
such criticisms likely will set the tone when delegates of the 
750000member aft meet in boston beginning monday and the 2 
millionmember nea gathers in kansas city later this week 
in separate interviews at their washington headquarters aft 
president albert shanker and nea chief geiger said they intend to 
challenge the president governors and other politicians to match 
their nice words about education with deeds and dollars 
each also said their unions have found more common ground than 
at any time in their history 
both shanker and geiger say they have quietly developed a 
personal and professional relationship unimaginable a few years 
ago they make it a point to eat lunch together at washingtons 
trendy i ricci restaurant to talk over educational and union issues 
the cold wars over here too shanker said keith geiger 
and i get along well personally thats a relationship that hasnt 
been there for a long time 
shanker 62 said he even dreams of putting the two unions on 
the path to merger before he retires some day as president 
the aft and nea are two unions that have bucked the trend of a 
decline in the union movement he said instead of competing 
against each other we should figure out how to pull together 
people who are in educational functions in american industry you 
could have a new american labor movmenent based on information and 
professional workers 
but neither merger nor shankers retirement appear imminent 
hes running for a ninth twoyear term as president at his 
