<TEXT>
the chicago board of trade has a selling job to 
do even if federal regulators approve the exchanges request to 
trade insurance risk alongside soybeans and treasury bonds 
some people in the insurance industry expressed skepticism 
tuesday about the proposal to trade reinsurance futures the 
exchange argued that the innovative products would allow insurers 
to stabilize underwriting risks resulting in lower insurance costs 
for consumers 
my general feeling would be a waitandsee attitude said 
dan kummer vice president of administration and finance in the 
business insurance division of allstate insurance co 
from my point of view im not sure i would see this as a 
replacement for some kinds of reinsurance kummer said in a 
telephone interview from allstates headquarters in suburban 
northbrook 
but burton gutterman a board of trade director told a news 
conference the insurance industry will embrace the products once it 
learns how to use them just as onceskeptical banks have become 
regular traders of the exchanges interestrate futures 
there are a lot of questions that have to be answered he 
said thats a process the board of trade is committed to 
pursuing 
gutterman said the exchange on monday submitted proposals for 
two reinsurance contracts to the commodity futures trading 
commission for approval 
the contracts would offer insurers a new way to reduce their 
risk on auto and health insurance policies while creating new 
markets for speculators 
reinsurance is the practice among insurance companies of selling 
policies to other insurers reinsurers to spread the risk around 
the proposed futures contracts would be agreements for future 
deliveries of reinsurance certificates based on pools of auto and 
health insurance policies the value of a contract would represent 
the difference between the premiums collected and claims paid on 
the pool of policies 
in an unusual twist the board of trade would employ a central 
custodian to inspect and qualify all policies 
the custodian also would act as a clearinghouse for information 
about premiums and claims theoretically providing all market 
participants with a level playing field the exchange said in a 
statement 
the board of trade said that by buying and selling the 
contracts insurers could effectively reinsure some of their 
policies through the exchange 
the insurance markets represent a huge financial sector that 
currently has very limited ways by which to manage its considerable 
risk board of trade chairman karsten mahlmann said in a 
statement 
gutterman said that pending cftc approval of the contracts the 
board of trade would lobby state insurance commissioners to allow 
insurers in their states to use the contracts for reinsurance 
kevin hennosy a spokesman for the national association of 
insurance commissioners said he had not seen the board of trade 
proposals 
we certainly would have an interest in how this would impact 
the consumer and how such a proposal would be regulated hennosy 
said from his office in kansas city mo 
