<TEXT>
news that atampts secondquarter profit will be 
lower than a year ago and below analysts expectations sent the 
price of the nations most widely held stock sliding wednesday 
the announcement by american telephone amp telegraph co was the 
first time since the 1984 breakup of the former bell system that 
the nations largest phone company has given advance warning of a 
lower profit 
the company blamed the expected earnings slide in the quarter 
ending saturday partly on lowerthanexpected sales of telephone 
equipment 
atampt would not predict how much the drop would be it said it 
would release secondquarter results in midjuly 
analysts said the news was surprising but they did not doubt 
atampts forecast that profit for the entire year would be at a 
record high 
all this suggests to me is a temporary profit margin 
squeeze with a reversal over the next six months said stuart 
crane who follows atampt for the investment firm gruntal amp co 
the fundamentals of atampt are strong he said i dont 
agree with throwing out the stock 
in nationwide new york stock exchange trading atampt shares 
closed at 3912 down 212 from tuesdays close earlier the 
shares were down as much as 350 about 115 million shares 
changed hands wednesday nearly nine times the average daily volume 
atampt estimates it has 25 million shareholders more than any 
other us company about 40 percent of the shares are held by 
individuals 
atampt spokesman dick gray said results from april and may 
indicate sales to us businesses of equipment such as electronic 
switchboards and private phone systems have been unexpectedly low 
sales of products to telephone operating companies such as 
switching equipment also have been less than anticipated gray 
said as have been sales to the federal government 
atampt also said sales in its computer division have lagged 
the company said the lower equipment sales were due to market 
conditions and a sluggish economy 
atampt does not disclose how much of its profit it derives from 
individual business segments 
meanwhile heavy demand for atampts new universal card has caused 
expenses associated with processing applications for the credit 
card to rise the company said 
atampt called demand for the card twice the level expected the 
card which combines a phone charge card with a mastercard or visa 
was introduced in march 
the company said the expected decline in secondquarter earnings 
will make it more difficult to meet its objective of 10 percent to 
12 percent profit growth this year but it stands by its earlier 
projection that net income for all of 1990 will break last years 
record high in 1989 atampt earned 27 billion or 250 a share 
on revenue of 36 billion 
for several years atampt has been cutting costs by reducing 
employment levels 
in april atampt reached agreement with its unions to offer early 
retirement to about 34000 workers the program follows one offered 
last year to managers under which about 12000 opted for early 
retirement atampt has about 315000 employees 
atampt also plans to continue to move workers into sales and 
marketing jobs to increase revenue gray said 
george kelly an analyst at morgan stanley amp co attributed the 
slowdown in sales of corporate phone systems partly to the 
nationwide commercial real estate slump as fewer companies move to 
new quarters fewer phone systems are sold he said 
atampt also faces increased competition in the office phone market 
from rolm which is owned by international business machines corp 
and siemens ag of west germany kelly said 
in the market for centraloffice switches the nerve center of 
phone companies atampt has seen increased competition from lm 
ericsson of sweden kelly said 
gruntals crane said demand for centraloffice switches has 
softened as the regional phone operating companies have completed a 
cycle of buying new equipment but he predicted an upturn in two to 
three years as atampt comes out with new opticalbased central 
switches the company is several years ahead of competitors in this 
advanced technology he said 
