<TEXT>
apparel manufacturer salant corp sought refuge 
in bankruptcy court wednesday after struggling unsuccessfully with 
debts incurred in buying a larger rival two years ago 
it was the second filing under chapter 11 of the federal 
bankruptcy code for the new yorkbased clothing company whose 
nationally known brands include dr denton sleepwear john henry 
shirts and lady manhattan sportswear 
salant attributed its troubles to weakness in the retail 
business at a time of year that is always the slowest for the 
company 
the fate of salant furnished another example of what can happen 
when companies fail to generate enough cash to pay for takeovers 
financed with borrowed money the retail industry on which salant 
relies for its business has had its share of victims including 
campeau corps federated and allied department store divisions and 
ames department stores inc 
ray w williams salants chairman and chief executive said in 
a news release that continued softness in the retail apparel 
market during the traditional low point of our seasonal business 
has made it impossible for us to satisfy our obligations to our 
lenders on a timely basis 
the bankruptcy filing was foreshadowed in midjune when salant 
diclosed discussions with lenders about refinancing its debts 
that news came as salant revealed it was in default on 108 
million in principal and interest on bank loans and couldnt cover 
19 million due on certain bonds 
the company said then that it was looking into alternatives 
including a second bankruptcy filing 
salant emerged from its first bankruptcy case three years ago 
shortly thereafter it began building a stake in manhattan 
industries inc a much bigger competitor that it eventually bought 
for 105 million in the spring of 1988 
retail analysts said there has been a perception within the 
trade that salant undertook too big a task when it bought manhattan 
in an effort to broaden its line of national brands 
until the takeover salant mainly made private label clothing 
for retailers such as sears roebuck and co and jc penney co it 
also has the thomson trouser co 
in buying manhattan salant gained ownership of various perry 
ellis lines manhattan shirts lady manhattan sportswear and the 
vera label of scarves and other items 
the pessimism about salants prospects have been reflected in 
the companys stock price it closed at 287 a share in composite 
new york stock exchange trading wednesday off 25 cents from 
tuesday and down from a high of 2687 in the last 52 weeks 
salants firstquarter loss widened to 23 million from the 
427000 loss a year earlier 
edward johnson director of the johnson redbook service of 
prescott ball amp turben inc in new york said salants chairman 
overreached in buying manhattan and in retrospect paid too high a 
price 
his appetite was a little too strong johnson said 
still he believes williams stands a decent chance of turning 
salant around he noted that williams proved himself an able 
manager as president of the farah manufacturing co 
hes a capable man said johnson 
in the news release williams said the company believes it can 
continue operating effectively while negotiating with its creditors 
and attempting a courtsupervised reorganization salants denton 
mills inc subsidiary was included in the bankruptcy filing 
he said the cit groupfactoring has agreed to forward 100 
million in working capital to salant an arrangement which must be 
approved by the bankruptcy court cit is a company that acts as a 
financial middleman in transactions between apparel manufacturers 
and retailers 
alan millstein publisher of the new york newsletter fashion 
network report said salant has had a history of missteps with the 
manhattan takeover only the latest misbegotten maneuver 
it was a case of a minnow swallowing a whale and nearly 
choking to death on it millstein said the acquisition of 
manhattan industries was almost a total disaster the perry ellis 
name was very costly 
salant unloaded moneylosing portions of perry ellis since the 
1988 acquisition and only retained the profitable licenses 
millstein said in the 1960s salant had a shot at becoming as 
powerful a force in mens wear as levi strauss amp co became with 
blue jeans sales volumes of the two companies were running neck 
and neck 
salant missed its chance by not plunging deeply into denim as 
levi did millstein said 
