smith will consist of 10 to 12 attorneys from the fdic and rtc it 
is aiming for a share of the 350 million set aside by the 
securities and exchange commission for claimants of drexel and the 
400 million set aside for claimants of milken 
drexel which sold investors billions of dollars worth of the 
risky highinterest debt securities known as junk bonds sought 
bankruptcy protection in federal court in new york in february a 
judge scheduled nov 15 as the deadline for bringing claims against 
the firm 
