<TEXT>
the west german economics minister on 
wednesday urged foreign companies to invest in east germany saying 
they would find a stable market and a bridge to east europe 
helmut haussmann made his statements at a meeting of the 
international chamber of commerce in hamburg as the giant west 
german electronics firm siemens announced it would invest 600 
million in east germany over the next three years 
meanwhile west germany said the last of the borders between the 
two germanies would fall sunday the day the two countries merge 
their economies and east germany sheds 40 years of socialism for 
freemarket rules 
full political union is now expected after allgerman elections 
suggested for early december the germanys after completing the 
treaty on economic merger are now working on one that would iron 
out the consitutional issues 
some experts say up to 4 million people could lose their jobs in 
east germany as industries once supported by the state fail in the 
open market more than onethird of businesses are expected to 
close 
an influx of western industry and goods could help offset the 
falling standard of living experts have said 
haussmann said he hoped the united states japan and all of 
europe would discover east germany which he said offered secure 
market conditions and a stable currency 
western companies have been reluctant to invest in east germany 
during the current political upheaval and transition to a market 
economy 
east german economics minister gerhard pohl also at the hamburg 
meeting said that of the 2000 joint venture agreements east 
germany had signed so far with western companies less than 5 
percent were with nonwest german companies 
in arguing for investment in east germany haussmann said the 
country would be a member of both the european economic community 
and comecon east europes economic equivalent 
east germany is the bridge between the ec and comecon 
haussmann said make use of that bridge if you come too late 
you will miss out 
much of eastern europe has opened to new investment following 
last years rejection of repressive communist rule and subsequent 
democratic reforms 
the announcement by siemens would represent the biggest single 
investment since east germany implemented its reforms the company 
said it would have up to 30000 employees in what is now east 
germany within several years 
siemens manufacturers computers telecommunications equipment 
household appliances and other products the company said its east 
german projects would be in communications data processing energy 
and transportation technology plant automation medical technology 
and environmental protection 
the investment includes previously announced joint ventures with 
11 former government enterprises and a contract to upgrade east 
germanys poor telephone system in six major cities 
siemens spokesman eberhard posner said most new employees would 
be east germans half newly hired and the rest from existing east 
german companies 
in another step toward unification the bonn government said 
that on sunday for the first time germans would be able to travel 
from east to west without border controls 
in bonn government spokesman hans klein said west german 
interior minister wolfgang schaeuble and his east german 
counterpart petermichael diestel would meet along the border 
between east germany and bavaria on sunday to sign an agreement 
eliminating all frontier controls 
