<TEXT>
south korea has boosted its economic 
growth target for this year to 8 percent to 9 percent up sharply 
from 65 percent previously a government plan said wednesday 
the new target compares with actual growth of 67 percent last 
year when exports the engine of south koreas economic growth 
were sluggish 
the countrys economy grew at an annual average rate of 127 
percent between 1986 and 1988 when exports jumped by more than 20 
percent annually 
the new goal was contained in the economic plan for the second 
half of this year that was adopted tuesday in a meeting of economic 
ministers 
officials at the economic planning board said the upward 
revision was prompted by a betterthanexpected economic 
performance in the first half and an anticipated export recovery in 
the latter half 
the plan said the gross national product was estimated to have 
grown at a rate of 92 percent in the first half mainly spurred by 
strong private consumption and booming construction business 
according to the plan south korea is expected to post a current 
account deficit of 1 billion this year its first shortfall in 
five years the government previously had projected a surplus of 2 
billion for the year 
officials said the economic management plan calls for holding 
down annual price inflation to 9 percent by cooling down overheated 
domestic consumption and curbing hotel leisure and other 
unnecessary construction projects 
korean consumer prices have gone up an estimated 7 percent so 
far this year fueled by excessive demands for construction 
materials connected with a boom in real estate and excessive 
private consumption 
the annual inflation rate stood at 57 percent last year and 
averagd 38 percent in the preceding seven years a government 
think tank predicted two weeks ago that prices would rise 13 
percent this year 
the government plans to peg this years total money supply 
growth at 19 percent to contain inflation officials said 
